findings:
1. vLLM is adding GitHub stars ~3.6x faster than Ollama, and is a top-4 grower of all 65 tracked entities. Over the 27-day snapshot vLLM went 82,693 -> 85,653 (+2,960, +3.58%); Ollama 173,949 -> 175,684 (+1,735, +1.00%). vLLM's +3.58% is 4th of all 65 tracked entities — the three ahead (codex +6.0%, claude-code +3.58%, cloudflare +3.86% off a tiny 4k base) are AI coding tools / a small-base outlier, so vLLM is the fastest-growing genuine infra/serving project.
   - SQL: WITH b AS (SELECT entity_slug, value, captured_at, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY entity_slug ORDER BY captured_at ASC) rn_first, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY entity_slug ORDER BY captured_at DESC) rn_last FROM entity_stats WHERE metric='github_stars' AND entity_slug IN ('vllm','ollama')) SELECT entity_slug, MAX(value) FILTER (WHERE rn_first=1) first_val, MAX(value) FILTER (WHERE rn_last=1) last_val FROM b GROUP BY entity_slug;
   - Returned: ollama 173949->175684; vllm 82693->85653. Ranking (all entities, ORDER BY pct DESC): codex 6.02, cloudflare 3.86, claude-code 3.58, vllm 3.58, crewai 3.31, ... (ollama not in top 15; = 1.00%).

2. vLLM's share of the self-hosted-inference conversation has climbed from ~33% to ~45% (and 75% so far in July), overtaking Ollama's momentum. Distinct HN+lobsters stories/month: Feb vllm 8 / ollama 16; Mar 10/28; Apr 9/24; May 5/10; Jun 14/17; Jul(partial) 3/1. vLLM share of the two-horse race (vllm/(vllm+ollama)): Feb 33% -> Jun 45% -> Jul(partial) 75%. Ollama peaked in March (28) and has fallen.
   - SQL: SELECT to_char(date_trunc('month',source_created_at),'YYYY-MM') mo, count(DISTINCT url_hash) FILTER (WHERE jsonb_exists(entities,'vllm')) vllm, count(DISTINCT url_hash) FILTER (WHERE jsonb_exists(entities,'ollama')) ollama FROM raw_items WHERE source_slug IN ('hn_top','hn_new','hn_best','hn_show','hn_ask','lobsters') AND source_created_at >= '2026-01-01' GROUP BY 1 ORDER BY 1;
   - Returned: (2026-01) 1/10, (02) 8/16, (03) 10/28, (04) 9/24, (05) 5/10, (06) 14/17, (07) 3/1.

3. vLLM's overall share of voice across ALL tagged HN+lobsters stories doubled, Feb->Jun. Feb 8/2,965 = 0.27%; Jun 14/2,583 = 0.54%. Small in absolute terms (a niche infra tool) but a clean doubling; July partial denominator = 648.
   - SQL: SELECT to_char(date_trunc('month',source_created_at),'YYYY-MM') mo, count(DISTINCT url_hash) FILTER (WHERE entities IS NOT NULL AND jsonb_array_length(entities)>0) tagged_total FROM raw_items WHERE source_slug IN ('hn_top','hn_new','hn_best','hn_show','hn_ask','lobsters') AND source_created_at >= '2026-02-01' GROUP BY 1 ORDER BY 1;
   - Returned: 02:2965, 03:3296, 04:2917, 05:2490, 06:2583, 07:648.

4. vLLM's HN discussion punches above its volume — its stories are ~2.7x more likely to reach real traction than Ollama's. Feb–Jul, deduped by url_hash: vLLM-only = 44 stories, 5 reached peak_score >= 50 (11.4% hit-rate), avg score 19, max 269. Ollama-only = 92 stories, only 4 reached >= 50 (4.3% hit-rate), avg 22, max 633. Ollama gets talked about more often but most posts die; vLLM posts convert to substantive discussion at 2.7x the rate. (Caveat: over the full window avg scores are comparable and Ollama owns the single biggest spike (633); divergence is in hit-rate and sharpest recently: since May 1, vLLM's 21 stories averaged peak_score 22 / max 203 while Ollama's 28 averaged 3 / max 9.)
   - SQL: WITH d AS (SELECT DISTINCT ON (url_hash) url_hash, entities, peak_score FROM raw_items WHERE source_slug LIKE 'hn_%' AND source_created_at >= '2026-02-01' AND (jsonb_exists(entities,'vllm') OR jsonb_exists(entities,'ollama')) ORDER BY url_hash, peak_score DESC NULLS LAST) SELECT jsonb_exists(entities,'vllm') has_vllm, jsonb_exists(entities,'ollama') has_ollama, count(*) stories, round(avg(peak_score)) avg_score, max(peak_score) max_score, count(*) FILTER (WHERE peak_score>=50) ge50 FROM d GROUP BY 1,2;
   - Returned: ollama-only 92 stories/avg22/max633/ge50=4; vllm-only 44/avg19/max269/ge50=5; both 4/avg3/max5/ge50=0.

5. The PyPI wrinkle is a false alarm — do not use it against the thesis. vLLM PyPI weekly downloads drifted 1,333,870 (Jun 12) -> 1,144,630 (Jul 6), -14%, but the series is noisy CI/mirror-driven traffic oscillating 1.13–1.33M with no trend, and Ollama has no PyPI presence at all (ships as a Go binary via install script/Docker), so PyPI cannot compare the two. new_repos_weekly exists only for Ollama (360->354->397 over three weeks — flat-to-slightly-up); vLLM has no new_repos_weekly rows. Lean on stars + conversation + engagement hit-rate; treat PyPI and new_repos as non-comparable and omit from headline claims.
   - SQL: SELECT entity_slug, metric, captured_at::date d, value FROM entity_stats WHERE entity_slug IN ('vllm','ollama') AND metric IN ('pypi_downloads_weekly','new_repos_weekly') ORDER BY entity_slug, metric, captured_at;
   - Returned: ollama new_repos 06-22:360, 06-29:354, 07-06:397; vllm pypi 1.33M->1.14M drift; no vllm new_repos, no ollama pypi.
